Show HN: GitChat – ChatGPT for Code Reviews
text:
Hey all!

Understanding code changes and their implications is a tough and time-consuming problem for large PRs

What if ChatGPT did the work for you?

That's the concept behind GitChat (GitChat.co). Paste a public GitHub PR URL in and it will spin up a ChatGPT-like agent to answer questions about the code changes etc.

I've been experimenting with this and it has certainly sped up my flow. I'd imagine for OSS maintainers who look at hundreds of PRs per week this can be helpful in quickly distilling information and making decisions re: community-suggested changes.

Would love to hear folks' feedback.

More info here: https://twitter.com/mathemagic1an/status/1631762207913684993
